					<head>Karaite halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Three pieces of Yaʻqūb ibn Isḥāq Qirqisānī Kitāb al-Anwār wal-marāqib.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="168v"/>
							<title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-Anwār wal-marāqib </title>
							<title xml:lang="ara">كتاب الأنوار والمراقب</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/87812660">Qirqisānī, Yaʻqūb ibn Isḥāq, active 10th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="ara" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/87812660">قرقساني، يعقوب بن اسحق</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/87812660">אלקרקסאני, אבו יוסף יעקוב‏</persName>
							</author>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="105v"/>
								<title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-Anwār wal-marāqib</title>
								<note>
									<p>Portions of the 11th and 12th Maḳalat on the subject of forbidden marriages and the law of levirate, and forbidden meats, dress, seeds and on fringes.</p>
									<p>Quotes several Karaite authorities.</p>
									<p>Includes a complete index of the 42 chapters contained in this Maḳalah, folios <locus from="41r" to="44r"/>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="106r" to="160v"/>
								<title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-Anwār wal-marāqib</title>
								<note>
									<p>A fragment of Maḳalah 12, written in a different Arabic hand. </p>
									<p>The biblical quotations are given in the Hebrew characters.</p>
									<p>Has a substantial gap after folio 131 and a small gap after folio 111.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="161r" to="168v"/>
								<title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Kitāb al-Anwār wal-marāqib</title>
								<note>
									<p>A small fragment of Maḳalah 12, in another hand.</p>
									<p>Contains the whole chapter 33, together with some portions of chapter 32 and 34. </p>
									<p>The biblical quotations are given in the Arabic characters.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; three different Arabic hands of the 12 to 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>168 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>205/190</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>168 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of  mostly 10 leaves each. </p>
									<p>Quires numbered in part 1, i.e. nos. 13, 14, 15, 16.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Fragmentary all throughout. Defective at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Many leaves more or less mutilated.</p>
									<p>Gaps after folios: 1, 2, 8, 9, 17, 25, 27, 45, 55, 111, 131.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="11 16" writtenLines="11 16">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Three different Arabic hands of the 12 to 13th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="105v"/>, <locus from="106r" to="160v"/> and <locus from="161r" to="168v"/>- due to different but contemporary Arabic hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
